{"word":"δ.η.=τα","slug":"δ.η.=τα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n24506\" key=\"D.H.=ta\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">δῆτα</orth>, <pos opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pos\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Adv.\">Adv.</a></pos>, lengthd. and more emphatic form of <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">δή,</foreign> first as <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.l. in</abbr> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0016.tlg001.perseus-grc1:4:69\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hdt.\">Hdt.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.69</biblScope></bibl>, mostly used by Trag. and <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pl.\">Pl.</a></author> </bibl> (v. infr.).—Never placed at the beginning of a sentence or verse, exc. in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0011.tlg003.perseus-grc1:986\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ S.\">S.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Aj.\">Aj.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">986</biblScope></bibl>. <sense n=\"1\" id=\"n24506.0\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> in answers, mostly added to a word which echoes a statement or question, as <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἴσασιν ὅστις ἦρξε . .</foreign> Answ. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἴσασι δ.</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">aye</tr_> they know, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0006.tlg003.perseus-grc1:1373\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ E.\">E.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Med.\">Med.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1373</biblScope> </bibl>; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">γιγνώσκεθ᾽ ὑμεῖς . .;</foreign> Answ. <foreign lang=\"greek\