speech, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὥς μ᾽ ἀπώλεσας· ἀπώλεσας δ.</foreign> how hast thou destroyed me! —<tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">aye,</tr_> destroyed <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">indeed,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0011.tlg005.perseus-grc1:1164\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ S.\">S.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ El.\">El.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1164</biblScope> </bibl>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἰὼ δύστηνε σύ, δύστηνε δῆτα</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0011.tlg006.perseus-grc1:760\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Id.\">Id.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ph.\">Ph.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">760</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>); also to correct the previous speaker, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οἴκτιρέ θ᾽ ἡμᾶς . .</foreign> Answ. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οἴκτιρε δ . . . ἐκγόνους</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">nay rather</tr_> pity . ., <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0006.tlg012.perseus-grc1:673\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ E.\">E.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ El.\">El.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">673</biblScope></bibl>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0006.tlg012.perseus-grc1:676\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">676</biblScope> </bibl>; without repeating the word, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">αὐτὸς δ᾽ ἀναλοῖ δ.</quote_> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">yes truly . .,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0085.tlg004.perseus-grc1:814\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ A.\">A.</a></author> <title_ TE